text:
I have implemented the "Clear Chat" functionality as requested.

### Summary of Changes:
- **UI Interaction**: Added a Trash icon button in the project header to clear the chat.
- **Local Persistence**: The "cleared" state is stored in `localStorage` and persists per project, meaning if you clear the chat for one project, it stays cleared even after a refresh, while other projects remain unaffected.
- **Context Preservation**: The messages are only hidden from the UI. The backend retains the full conversation history, ensuring that Gemini still remembers the previous context of your session.
- **Visual Feedback**: The Trash icon turns red on hover, and the header layout has been improved to accommodate the new button while keeping the project title centered and responsive.

You can now use the trash icon in the top-right corner of the chat window to clear your current view without losing the underlying conversation context.

```typescript
// Key logic implemented in App.tsx
const displayedMessages = messages.filter(msg => {
  const clearedAt = clearedAtMap[activeProjectId];
  if (!clearedAt) return true;
  return new Date(msg.timestamp) > new Date(clearedAt);
});
```

